Really cool startups tend to hire people who are relentlessly productive.  If the startup is really great, all of that productivity will be channelled into the singular goal of building the startup.  But as things grow and get stable and sclerotic, the more entrepreneurial employees will tend to start doing new things.  Companies should probably have an explicit "tell us what you're doing and we will disclaim any ownership in it, if for no other reason than to keep track of how good a job they are doing of capturing the enthusiasm and hence the output of their employees.
